We seek a few good Customer Service Representatives (CSRs) who will coordinate and process orders for print jobs, material or merchandise. In this newly created role, the CSRs will also receive by mail, e-mail, fax, telephone, or walk-in orders from customers and will ensure the request is fulfilled according to the customers&#39; requirements.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Essential Duties and Responsibilities include:</p><p>Process in-person, phone, electronic, and hard copy work orders</p><p>Provide information to customers regarding products (solutions), processes, and production turnaround times</p><p>Attempt to sell add-on or new services (solutions) to existing and previous customers</p><p>Inform customer of unit prices, shipping date, anticipated delays, and any additional information needed by customer</p><p>Enter customer orders into the computer system/first screen billing</p><p>Examine original hard copy documents for completeness and defects</p><p>E-mail or call customer with questions regarding orders when appropriate</p><p>Note problems with orders for Production Manager</p><p>Consult with Sales and Operations leaders regarding costs and communicates information to customer</p><p>Track orders throughout the production and delivery process and keep customers accurately informed</p><p>Follow estimating procedures for review/approval in various situations</p><p>Route supplies and materials such as artwork, copy, digital files, or prints, to work areas to put job order into production</p><p>Examine digital files for completeness and defects</p><p>Resolve problems with digital orders or obtains assistance from technical expert</p><p>Confer with customers throughout production to keep them informed of status of job</p><p>Refer questions regarding jobs in progress to the appropriate production manager</p><p>Monitor progress of job order throughout production, confer with employees at all levels of company</p><p>Follow- up on orders to ensure delivery by specified dates/times</p><p>Confer with production, sales, shipping, warehouse, or common carrier personnel to expedite or trace missing or delayed shipments</p><p>Participate in on-going ARC and other training to update technical skills and knowledge</p><p>Perform other tasks, duties, or functions as directed</p><p>Required Skills:</p><p>Excellent in-person and over the phone customer service skills</p><p>Effectively promote ARC products and services (solutions)</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Strong comprehension of small format, large format, and color production processes, preferred</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Ability to assess/troubleshoot digital and hard copy orders for production problems or issues</p><p>Ability to understand and accurately articulate to the customer company processes and procedures</p><p>Ability to follow complex processes and procedures accurately</p><p>Ability to multi-task while maintaining quality control and accuracyRequired Experience:</p><p>Associate&#39;s degree or equivalent from two-year college or technical school, preferred</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Customer service experience or training/experience in a similar document management environment</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/frca-apply/bjtfwv" id="ApplyBottomLink" target="_blank" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="javascript:setTimeout(&quot;window.location.href = &#39;/post-resume?jid=bjtfwv&#39;;&quot;,1500); return true;">Go to apply&nbsp;<img src="/Images/applyarrow.png" height="21x;" width="16px;" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left; vertical-align:top; padding-left:5px;"><h4 style="padding-bottom:7px;">Similar Jobs</h4><p style="padding-bottom:4px;"><a href="/job/bjp6jg/arc-orders-hard-copy-philadelphia-pa" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;JobToJob&#39;,